## Limitations

The information gathered is primarily from secondary sources, which may include personal opinions and interpretations. The complexity of post-war events and the varying degrees of accountability for Nazis mean that some details may be oversimplified or generalized. Additionally, the clandestine nature of programs like Operation Paperclip means that some information may remain classified or incomplete.